The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Friday, June 10, 2005

 Course on films

 Reading Film, a film appreciation course for youth, presented by The Seagull Foundation for the Arts at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 6 pm. Participation by registration only.

 Decor

 An exhibition of jute products at Pragnananda Bhavan, Moulali, 3 pm to 9 pm.

 A furniture exhibition at Ice Skating Rink, 11 am to 8 pm. 

 On stage

 Mime play Lagaan, based on the songs of the film, at Landmark rooftop, 6.30 pm.

 Workshop

 A theatre workshop for children, organised by Indian Mime Theatre, at Entally Academy, 10 am to 6 pm.

 Lecture

 Dr SP Sen Memorial Lecture by Suranjan Das at Institute of Historical Studies, 5 pm.

 Art watch

 Summer exhibition, featuring works by eminent artists, at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.

 Inauguration of an exhibition of figurative paintings by Sabyasachi Sen at Genesis Art Gallery, 6 pm.

 Opening of Versus, a show of paintings and sculptures, at Gaganendra Pradarshashala, Calcutta Information Centre, 5 pm.

 An exhibition of works on Lord Buddha by contemporary artists at Gallery Katayun, 3.30 pm to 7.30 pm.

 Tranquility and Colour, showcasing Indian art and sculpture, at Idiyas Gallery, 10.30 am to 7.30 pm.

 A display of paintings, prints and sculptures at North Gallery, Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm.

 Annual group exhibition at New South Gallery, Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm.




